        <mxCell id="step10" value="10" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#1A73E8;strokeColor=#0B57D0;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontStyle=1;fontSize=15;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="665" y="905" width="30" height="30" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="note_chat" value="&lt;b&gt;Chat path — create &amp;amp; refine a watch&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;1  You describe a candidate trip in natural language in the Web UI.&#xa;2  Web UI authenticates via Cognito and calls the Agent API Gateway with the user JWT.&#xa;3  Agent Authorizer Lambda validates that JWT against Cognito JWKS.&#xa;4  Travel Agent (Strands) turns the request into a structured watch — Bedrock for&#xa;    NL understanding, S3 for multi-turn session state.&#xa;5  The watch is stored or patched in DynamoDB Watches." style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=12;fontSize=12;fontColor=#5A4A00;size=18;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="1140" width="760" height="250" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="note_poll" value="&lt;b&gt;Scheduled poll &amp;amp; alert pipeline&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;6  EventBridge cron fires the Poller Lambda.&#xa;7  Poller fetches flight + hotel prices via the flights/hotels MCP servers, signing a&#xa;    per-component JWT minted from Secrets Manager (ADR 0006).&#xa;8  Poller writes a FareHistory snapshot and reads active watches via the&#xa;    status-index GSI (ADR 0007).&#xa;9  Bedrock decides alert-worthiness — threshold or 30-day anomaly — with a&#xa;    written reason (ADR 0004).&#xa;10 On an alert the Poller async-invokes the Notifier → SES emails you;&#xa;    lastAlertedAt is written back to Watches (ADR 0005)." style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#D6B656;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=12;fontSize=12;fontColor=#5A4A00;size=18;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="820" y="1140" width="780" height="290" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
